'''Ayub Shah''', a son of [[Timur Shah]], ruled [[Afghanistan]] from 1819 to 1823. Second oldest son of Timor Shah. He killed his brother [[Ali Shah Durrani|Ali Shah]] for the throne. He only ruled two years, holding off his own brothers and the Barakzai and Indian tribes from nearby. He was imprisoned  by the [[Barakzai dynasty|Barakzai]] and his brother took the throne. Shortly losing it to Barakzai.

