The '''Khogyani''' ('''Khugyani''', '''Khogiani''','''Khugiani''','''Khakwani''') ({{lang-ps|'''خوګياڼي'''}}, {{lang-fa|'''خاکوانی'''}}) [[tribe]] is a [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] tribe of the [[Karlani]] or "Hill Tribes" branch. The Khogyani Tribe originated in the [[Khogyani District]] of [[Nangarhar Province]] and later in [[Ghazni Province]] of [[Afghanistan]]. Some of their clans are also settled in [[Khyber Pukhtunkhwa]], [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]] and [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] provinces of [[Pakistan]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
==Dynamics== The tribe is divided into three sub-tribes: the [[Kherbon]], the [[Wazir (Khogyani)|Wazir]], and the [[Shirzad tribe]].<ref>Afghan Information Centre. [http://digitalcommons.library.arizona.edu/objectviewer?o=uadc%3A%2F%2Fazu_nehafghan%2Fazu_acku_serial_ds371_2_m66_n104 Monthly Bulletin, 1989]. Peshawar, Pakistan. #104.</ref> The Khogianis have a long history of conflict with the neighboring [[Shinwari tribe|Shinwari]] and [[Ghilzai]] tribes. {{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
