{{Infobox language |name=Mondzi |nativename= |states=China |ethnicity=[[Yi people|Yi]] |speakers=2,000? |date=1983 |ref=<ref name=YYFC>YYFC. 1983. [handwritten manuscript], cited in Lama (2012)</ref> |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Lolo-Burmese languages|Lolo-Burmese]] |fam3=[[Mondzish languages|Mondzish]] |script= |iso3=none |glotto=mond1267 |glottorefname=Mondzi }}
'''Mondzi''' ('''Munji'''; autonym: ''{{IPA|mo˨˩ndʑi˨˩}}'', Chinese 曼子) is a [[Lolo-Burmese languages|Lolo-Burmese language]] spoken by the [[Yi people]] of China. Speakers are located mostly in [[Funing County, Yunnan]], China and [[Hà Giang Province]], Vietnam.
