{{Infobox language | name = Semelai | nativename = | states = [[Malaysia]] | region = [[Malay Peninsula]] | ethnicity = {{sigfig|6270|2}} (2008)<ref name=e18/> | speakers = 4,100 | date = 2009 | ref = e18 | familycolor = Austroasiatic | fam2 = [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] | fam3 = [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern Aslian]] | script= [[Latin script]] | iso3 = sza | glotto = seme1247 | glottorefname = Semelai }}
Semelai is an [[Austroasiatic language]] spoken in the Malay Peninsula. It belongs to the [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern]] branch of the [[Aslian language]] subgrouping. The Semelai reside predominantly around the Bera, Serting and associated river systems in the states of [[Pahang]], [[Negeri Sembilan]] and [[Johor]].
== Phonology == Semelai has 32 consonants and 20 vowels.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=Q2V2sDpzOC0C&oi=fnd&pg=PR16&dq=Semelai+language&ots=F6v35v6ofW&sig=2AOFpYEOcBMgyiJoIPl4iDSX1jM#v=onepage&q=Semelai%20language&f=false|title=A Grammar of Semelai|last=Kruspe|first=Nicole|date=2004-04-08|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521814973|language=en}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |+Consonants ! colspan="2" rowspan="2" | ! colspan="3" |[[Bilabial consonant|Bilabial]] ! colspan="3" |[[Alveolar consonant|Alveolar]] ! colspan="3" |[[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] ! colspan="2" |[[Velar consonant|Velar]] ! rowspan="2" |[[Glottal consonant|Glottal]] |- !<small>plain</small> ![[Aspirated consonant|<small>aspirated</small>]] ![[Glottalization|<small>preglottalized</small>]] !<small>plain</small> ![[Aspirated consonant|<small>aspirated</small>]] ![[Glottalization|<small>preglottalized</small>]] !<small>plain</small> ![[Aspirated consonant|<small>aspirated</small>]] ![[Glottalization|<small>preglottalized</small>]] !<small>plain</small> ![[Aspirated consonant|<small>aspirated</small>]] |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Stop consonant|Stop]] !<small>voiceless</small> |p |pʰ | |t |tʰ | |c |cʰ | |k |kʰ |ʔ |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] |b | | |d | | |ɟ | | |g | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Fricative consonant|Fricative]] | | | |s | | | | | | | |h |- ! rowspan="2" |[[Nasal consonant|Nasal]] !<small>voiceless</small> |m̥ | | |n̥ | | | | | |ŋ̊ | | |- ![[Voice (phonetics)|<small>voiced</small>]] |m | |ʔm |n | |ʔn |ɲ | |ʔɲ |ŋ | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Approximant consonant|Approximant]] | | | |l | |ʔl |j | |ʔj |w | | |- ! colspan="2" |[[Trill consonant|Trill]] | | | |r | |ʔr | | | | | | |}
