{{Infobox Ethnic group |group = Uruguayans in Sweden |image = |popplace = [[Stockholm]], [[Gothenburg]], [[Malmö]] |langs = [[Spanish language]], [[Swedish language]] |rels = Predominantly [[Roman Catholicism]] |population=4,000 estimated}}
'''Uruguayans in Sweden''' are people born in [[Uruguay]] who live in [[Sweden]], or Swedish-born people of Uruguayan descent. As of 2013, there were over 4,000 Uruguayans living in Swedish territory.<ref name="Uruguaydelnorte">{{cite web |url=http://www.elpais.com.uy/domingo/suecia-uruguay-norte.html |title=Suecia: Uruguay del norte |date=8 September 2013 |publisher=[[El País (Uruguay)|EL PAIS]]}} {{es icon}}</ref>
==Overview== Being Sweden a very democratic country and a net receiver of immigrants, during the [[civic-military dictatorship of Uruguay]] (1973–1985) there were several Uruguayans that went exiled to Sweden; this was possible, among others, much because of Ambassador [[Harald Edelstam]].<ref name="Uruguaydelnorte"/> Nowadays there are many Uruguayans who still live in Sweden.<ref name="Uruguaydelnorte"/>
Uruguayan residents in Sweden have their own institutions, for instance, [[Casa Uruguay]] in [[Malmö]]<ref>[http://www.casauruguaymalmo.se/ Casa Uruguay Malmö] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104034953/http://www.casauruguaymalmo.se/ |date=2013-11-04 }} {{es icon}}</ref> and the Consultative Councils in [[Stockholm]] and [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.d20.org.uy/Lista-de-Consejos |title=List of Consultative Councils of Uruguayans abroad |accessdate=1 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130809011138/http://www.d20.org.uy/Lista-de-Consejos |archive-date=9 August 2013 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }} {{es icon}}</ref>
==Notable people== ;past * [[Dahd Sfeir]] (1932–2015), actress ;present * [[Henry Engler]] (born 1946 in Paysandú), neuroscientist, former [[Tupamaro]]<!-- see [[:es:Henry Engler]] --> * [[Lorena Giménez]] (born 1978 in Stockholm), writer * [[Martin Lopez]] (born 1978 in Stockholm), drummer * [[Roberto Mascaró]] (born 1948 in Montevideo), poet and translator<!-- see [[:es:Roberto Mascaró]] --> * [[Fernando Flores Morador]] (born 1950 in Montevideo), philosopher and historian of ideas<!-- see [[:es:Fernando Flores Morador]] --> * [[Martin Mendez]] (born 1978 in Montevideo), bass guitar player * [[Guillermo Molins]] (born 1988 in Montevideo), footballer * [[Sofía Rito]] (born 1985 in Stockholm), weightlifter * [[Sebastian Senatore]] (born 1985 in Montevideo), footballer * [[Ana Luisa Valdés]] (born 1953 in Montevideo), anthropologist and translator<!-- http://pechakuchamontevideo.org/ana-luisa-valdes-i-antropologia/ and article "Uruguay of the North" - see also [[:de:Ana Luisa Valdés]] --> * [[Hebert Abimorad]] ( born 1946 in Montevideo), poet and journalist
